abstract:
  The licenses accompanying most of the softwares dictate what you're allowed to do.
  That is theoretically unfeasible because ideally creativity whether good (or bad) shouldn't and can't be encumbered.
  No one should be dictating, heck even attempt to predict what you can do.
  Therefore, this `NotNot 0.1` license only says what you're NOT permitted to do.

Main:

- The following accompanies what should be the 'formal' and 'legal' statements of this 'license text'. The only permitted        license term allowed is '(The) NotNot LICENSE.'
Throughout this text, it will be referred to simply as, 'this license'.
- You CAN NOT prevent others' from having fair and reasonable access to the (source) code of your derivative work of this license. Additional variations of this license will be released in the future permitting users in doing so.
- There is no connection or obligation of any kind, of you, with others who provide code under this license.
examples exclude but are not limited to things like;
warranty claims, monetary compensation, lawsuits, damages etc. resulting from you using other works released under the terms of this license.
- You are NOT permitted to distribute sources under terms of this license without a copy of this license text. Modification of the license text while distribution is NOT permitted.
